# mbsyncrc based on
# http://www.ict4g.net/adolfo/notes/2014/12/27/EmacsIMAP.html
# ACCOUNT INFORMATION
IMAPAccount gregheiman02@gmail.com
# Address to connect to
Host imap.gmail.com
User gregheiman02@gmail.com
PassCmd "gpg2 -q --for-your-eyes-only --no-tty -d ~/.emacs.d/email/.mbsyncpass-acc1.gpg"
AuthMechs LOGIN
SSLType IMAPS
SSLVersions TLSv1.2
CertificateFile /etc/pki/tls/certs/ca-bundle.crt

# THEN WE SPECIFY THE LOCAL AND REMOTE STORAGE
# - THE REMOTE STORAGE IS WHERE WE GET THE MAIL FROM (E.G., THE
#   SPECIFICATION OF AN IMAP ACCOUNT)
# - THE LOCAL STORAGE IS WHERE WE STORE THE EMAIL ON OUR COMPUTER

# REMOTE STORAGE (USE THE IMAP ACCOUNT SPECIFIED ABOVE)
IMAPStore gregheiman02@gmail.com-remote 
Account gregheiman02@gmail.com 

# LOCAL STORAGE (CREATE DIRECTORIES with mkdir -p ~/Maildir/gregheiman02@gmail.com)
MaildirStore gregheiman02@gmail.com-local
SubFolders Verbatim
Path ~/Mail/gregheiman02@gmail.com/
Inbox ~/Mail/gregheiman02@gmail.com/INBOX

# CONNECTIONS SPECIFY LINKS BETWEEN REMOTE AND LOCAL FOLDERS
#
# CONNECTIONS ARE SPECIFIED USING PATTERNS, WHICH MATCH REMOTE MAIl
# FOLDERS. SOME COMMONLY USED PATTERS INCLUDE:
#
# 1 "*" TO MATCH EVERYTHING
# 2 "!DIR" TO EXCLUDE "DIR"
# 3 "DIR" TO MATCH DIR

Channel gregheiman02@gmail.com
Far :gregheiman02@gmail.com-remote:
Near :gregheiman02@gmail.com-local:
Patterns * ![GMAIL]* "INBOX" "[Gmail]/Sent Mail" "[Gmail]/All Mail" "[Gmail]/Trash" "[Gmail]/Starred"
Expunge Both
Create Both
SyncState *

# GROUPS PUT TOGETHER CHANNELS, SO THAT WE CAN INVOKE
# MBSYNC ON A GROUP TO SYNC ALL CHANNELS
#
# FOR INSTANCE: "mbsync gmail" GETS MAIL FROM
# "gmail-inbox", "gmail-sent", and "gmail-trash"
#
Group gregheiman02@gmail.com


